unita%20Williams%20Home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBillionaire%20Elon%20Musk%20on%20Tuesday%20(local%20time)%20said%20that%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20had%20asked%20him%20to%20facilitate%20the%20return%20of%20the%20two%20Boeing%20Starliner%20astronauts%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20Butch%20Wilmore%2C%20who%20have%20been%20on%20the%20space%20station%20since%20June%202024%2C%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SpaceX%20CEO%20claimed%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bterrible%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20pair%20were%20left%20%26quot%3Bstranded%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20by%20former%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20administration%20for%20so%20long%2C%20even%20though%20NASA%20had%20already%20roped%20in%20SpaceX%20months%20ago%20to%20return%20both%20astronauts%20as%20part%20of%20its%20Crew-9%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20%40POTUS%20has%20asked%20%40SpaceX%20to%20bring%20home%20the%202%20astronauts%20stranded%20on%20the%20%40Space_Station%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20We%20will%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPOTUS%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40POTUS%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpaceX%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40SpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20bring%20home%20the%202%20astronauts%20stranded%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSpace_Station%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40Space_Station%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20We%20will%20do%20so.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnTerrible%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20left%20them%20there%20so%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20(%40elonmusk)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1884365928038563880%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2028%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTerrible%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration%20left%20them%20there%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20has%20continuously%20said%20that%20astronauts%20are%20not%20stranded%20and%20that%20they%20are%20healthy%2C%20and%20in%20good%20spirits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20launched%20to%20the%20ISS%20aboard%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20in%20June%202024.%20The%20flight%2C%20which%20was%20intended%20to%20last%20only%2010%20days%2C%20experienced%20a%20rocky%20journey.%20After%20arriving%20at%20the%20space%20station%2C%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20worked%20for%20weeks%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20problems%20in%20the%20spacecraft%20but%20it%20was%20ultimately%20decided%20that%20it%20was%20too%20risky%20to%20return%20the%20Startliner%20with%20the%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20this%2C%20in%20August%202024%2C%20the%20space%20agency%20announced%20that%20it%20had%20asked%20SpaceX%20to%20bring%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20home%20aboard%20the%20SpaceX%20Crew-9%20capsule.%20The%20two%20astronauts%20were%20slotted%20into%20Crew-9%2C%20with%20NASA%20removing%20two%20of%20the%20four%20crew%20members%20who%20were%20set%20to%20launch%20on%20the%20SpaceX%20Dragon%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20only%20an%20astronaut%20and%20cosmonaut%20were%20launched%20aboard%20that%20flight%20to%20make%20room%20for%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%2C%20who%20were%20set%20to%20return%20home%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20expedition%20in%20February%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20another%20delay%20in%20December%2C%20because%20SpaceX%20needed%20more%20time%20to%20work%20on%20the%20latest%20Dragon%20spacecraft%2C%20which%20will%20be%20debuting%20with%20the%20launch%20of%20Crew-10.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20Crew-9%2C%20including%20the%20two%20Boeing%20astronauts%2C%20would%20not%20be%20back%2