four%20actions%20I%20took%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20ensure%20that%20my%20transitions%20between%20managers%20were%20smooth%20and%20helped%20me%20earn%20their%20trust.%20These%20pointers%20helped%20me%20stand%20out%20and%20grow%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220195eb9e-f474-4add-965e-ccd30521499d%5C%22%3E1.%20Own%20your%20career%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20approached%20my%20career%20with%20the%20mindset%20that%20I%20am%20responsible%20for%20it%20and%20my%20manager%20is%20a%20facilitator.%20That%20mental%20mode%20ensures%20I%20am%20communicating%20before%20I%20am%20asked%20to%20and%20seeking%20guidance%20from%20people%20beyond%20my%20immediate%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20habit%20of%20spending%20about%20two%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehours%20each%20month%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-product-manager-got-overseas-transfer-india-us-oracle-swe-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20reach%20out%20to%20multiple%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Amazon%20to%20ask%20about%20how%20they%20grow%20in%20their%20careers%20and%20get%20feedback%20on%20how%20I%20could%20do%20things%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb0a47b5-3e19-4909-8c29-3398495ee87a%5C%22%3E2.%20Document%20everything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20maintain%20a%20brag%20sheet%20with%20a%20log%20of%20all%20my%20achievements%20and%20summaries%20of%20all%20the%20projects%20I%20worked%20on%2C%20including%20the%20feedback%20from%20my%20previous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-valuable-company-employee-success-growth-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%20and%20team%20leads%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20any%20stakeholders.%20I%20set%2030%20to%2045%20minutes%20aside%20every%20week%20or%20two%20weeks%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20am%20not%20missing%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20mobility%20in%20tech.%20If%20people%20you%20worked%20with%20in%20the%20past%20year%20leave%2C%20there%20is%20nobody%20to%20vouch%20for%20your%20work.%20My%20performance%20rating%20suffered%20once%20when%20I%20worked%20under%20three%20managers%20who%20all%20had%20different%20perceptions%20of%20what%20I%20worked%20on%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20take%20any%20active%20steps%20to%20rectify%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20share%20this%20document%20with%20my%20all%20of%20my%20new%20managers%20so%20they%20have%20my%20track%20record%20on%20hand%20and%20have%20context%20on%20all%20of%20my%20current%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c85d8b2-1cfa-4f48-93a0-63cd5671939f%5C%22%3E3.%20Prepare%20for%20one-on-ones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20started%20my%20career%2C%20I%20used%20to%20wing%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-on-one-weekly-meeting-with-boss-mistakes-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20one-on-one%20meetings%20with%20my%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20got%20very%20little%20out%20of%20these%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20taking%20the%20initiative%20to%20set%20up%20introductory%20conversations%20with%20all%20my%20new%20managers%2C%20where%20I%20share%20my%20short-term%20and%20long-term%20goals.%20I%20also%20share%20the%20brag%20document%20I%20keep%20in%20this%20call%20to%20give%20them%20an%20overview%20of%20where%20I%20am%20with%20my%20career%20and%20what%20my%20current%20projects%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20first%20meeting%2C%20I%20switched%20to%20a%20different%20format%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20sessions.%20I%20borrowed%20from%20a%20book%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Art%20of%20Meeting%20with%20Your%20Manager%26quot%3B%20and%20broke%20my%20meetings%20into%20six%20sections.%20I%20tweak%20this%20according%20to%20different%20managers%20and%20their%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EIcebreaker%3A%20To%20ease%20into%20conversation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEmployee%20section%3A%20I%20share%20recent%20contributions%20my%20manager%20might%20not%20have%20on%20their%20radar%2C%20challenges%20I%20faced%2C%20and%20updates%20on%20discussions%20I%20have%20had%20with%20others%20in%20my%20team.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EManager%20section%3A%20I%20proactively%20ask%20for%20feedback.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDevelopment%20and%20growth%3A%20We%20discuss%20where%20I%20stand%20currently%20and%20brainstorm%20ideas%20and%20projects%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20am%20filling%20those%20gaps%20to%20meet%20the%20criteria%20for%20the%20next%20employee%20level.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAlign%20priorities%3A%20We%20discuss%20what%20I%20should%20work%20on%20immediately.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAction%20items%3A%20My%20manager%20and%20I%20both%20note%20down%20our%20action%20items%20for%20the%20next%20meeting%20and%20follow-up%20on%20any%20action%20items%20from%20the%20previous%20meeting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22454c258a-5dfd-445e-ad33-7a9c98740e78%5C%22%3E4.%20Divide%20and%20conquer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20grew%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20started%20taking%20on%20more%20leadership%20responsibilities.%20I%20began%20supporting%20new%20engineers%20on%20my%20team%20through%20one-on-ones%20and%20set%20up%20Slack%20channels%20where%20they%20could%20ask%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollaboration%20with%20other%20teams%20definitely%20changed.%20My%20manager%20and%20I%20divided%20and%20conquered.%20I%20would%20take%20the%20ownership%20of%20five%20to%20six%20teams%20and%20my%20manager%20would%20handle%20three%20to%20four.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20trying%20to%20see%20myself%20as%20a%20support%20system%20for%20my%20manager%20instead%20of%20someone%20just%20working%20under%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-work-with-many-managers-well-big-tech-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738108802000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6786055050dfd88e193e2d78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-work